A WOMAN who went missing on Shetland sparking a major search has been found safely.
A Coastguard helicopter and a lifeboat were involved in the operation to find Leigha Williamson, 44, after she disappeared from her home in Scalloway on Tuesday morning.
Police Scotland’s Paul Daley said: “We would like to extend gratitude to Coastguard and Lifeboat crews and volunteers for their assistance in today’s search efforts. 
“We would also like to thank the media and members of the public who shared our appeal for Ms Williamson.” 
